data.content:
Three things break in EF Core 10. Here's each one and the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` ‚Äî now takes a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your entire `Expression.Lambda` / `Expression.Call` machinery won't compile. Replace it with a simple lambda:

```csharp
// .NET 10 ‚Äî no expression trees needed
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

---

### 2. Complex type column names ‚Äî two changes

**a) Duplicate property names across complex types are now uniquified.** Your `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` will get auto-generated disambiguated column names (e.g. `Street1`). Pin the old names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b => {
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, a => {
        a.Property(x => x.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street");
    });
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, a => {
        a.Property(x => x.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street");
    });
});
```

**b) Nested complex types now use full path in column names.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was `BillingAddress_City`, now becomes `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. Pin old names with `HasColumnName()` to avoid a generated migration that renames columns.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` ‚Äî new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method (e.g. `CommandReaderExecuting`) now requires an additional `string logCommandText` parameter:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ‚Üê new: redacted SQL for safe logging
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (constants may be redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for the actual SQL
    }
}
```

Update **all** methods in the interface similarly (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.).
